FBIS3-35621 "drsov020_f_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 National Affairs Meshkov Holds News Conference on Victory Proposes Referendum on Independence LD3101101394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 31 Jan 94 LD3101101394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Yuriy Meshkov, elected president of Crimea on 30 January, has spoken in favor of holding a referendum on independence. In an interview with journalists he proposed that the referendum be held on 27 March, Interfax reports. Meanwhile, Nikolay Bagrov, who lost the Crimean presidential election, believes that a referendum would destabilize the situation in the region and aggravate relations between Ukraine and Russia.
